HEADWORD: Heaves
<hw>Heaves</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A disease of horses,
characterized by difficult breathing, with heaving of the flank,
wheezing, flatulency, and a peculiar cough; broken wind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heavily</ent>⟦br⟧
